# Brand Guidelines (source of truth)

Canonical file: `NextGenMove_Brand_Guidelines.html` (repo root). Design tokens in `src/styles/tokens.css` must match it. Do not invent new colors, fonts, or radii.

## Color

- **Ink** `#1A1A18` — primary text + primary CTA fill
- **Purple** `#3C3489` / **Purple Strong** `#4B3F9C` — brand moments, eyebrows, Track B
- **Amber** `#C97A2E` — warm counter-accent (stats, secondary emphasis)
- **Green** `#27500A` — success/positive only
- **Oxblood** `#8B3A3A` — warning/churned only
- Neutrals: bg `#FAFAF7`, surface `#FFFFFF`, surface-2 `#F1EFE8`, border `#E7E4D9`, muted `#9B9A91`, secondary `#6B6A63`
- Tint backgrounds: purple `#EEEDFE`, amber `#FAEEDA`, green `#EAF3DE`, oxblood `#F5E9E7`

## Gradients

- **Horizon** (indigo→amber, 115°) — signature; **one full-bleed use per screen** (hero/cover only). Never on buttons + tags + hero together.
- **Dusk** — quiet card emphasis / empty states
- **Route** — thin 2–4px progress/underline accents only

## Typography

- Display: **Playfair Display** (headlines, testimonials italic) — never body copy
- UI: **Inter**
- Eyebrows/labels: **JetBrains Mono**, uppercase, purple, ~11px

## Layout

- App content lives in a centered **PageFrame** (`--page-max: 64rem`) with border + light shadow — never edge-to-edge full viewport width
- Cards/forms: tight padding (8–14px); prefer compressed density over large empty gaps

## Components

- Primary button = Ink fill; Brand button = Purple; Outline = Ink border; radius ~7px
- Status pills = tint bg + full-strength text (never solid pill fills)
- Avatars = initials in purple/amber/green (hash by name) — no stock photos of people
- Cards: tight padding/gaps (8–14px); radius ~8–10px

## Do / Don't

- DO: Horizon once at top as full-bleed banner
- DON'T: Multiple gradients on one screen
- DO: Density that reads as precision
- DON'T: Large empty “breathing room” gaps that dilute the itinerary feel
- DON'T: Stock photography or generic illustrated people
